1. for whatever: whatever choose the coordination randomly and put the mark on the board.
   for clever: the clever player tries to make a move by placing its mark in the first available position,
               iterating column by column, until a valid move is made
   for genius: tries to make a move by iterating over the board, avoiding occupied positions and putting
               the mark next to same mark on the same row or the same column.

2. Implementing a common interface in all player classes allows for polymorphism and encapsulation.
  Polymorphism occurs because each player has identical methods but performs differently than the others.
  Encapsulation ensures each class takes on its own responsibility.